* Add -g flag when compiling with gcc.

* lay next
	---
	After running this command, hit enter several times(repeating the command) to switch between display layouts.

* Difference between 'print' and 'display':
	- 'display' enables automatic displaying of certain expressions each time gdb stops at a breakpoint or after a step.
	- 'print' prints the content of variable/memory location/register.

* watch <where>
	---
	Sets a new watchpoint. It can be set on a variable, then each time it changes will be caught. 

* x/[format] [address expression]
	---
	Displays the memory contents at a given address using the specified format.
